<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:58:36 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>国家美术馆接受了借阅图书馆的新角色，感谢向其他博物馆发送艺术品的大礼</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-national-gallery-of-art-embraces-new-role-as-lending-library-thanks-to-a-big-gift-that-sends-artwork-to-other-museums-180988597/</link><description>长期受托人米切尔·P·拉尔斯 (Mitchell P. Rales) 的家族基金会捐赠 1.16 亿美元，用于分享博物馆的藏品，以纪念美国 250 岁生日</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 21:03:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-national-gallery-of-art-embraces-new-role-as-lending-library-thanks-to-a-big-gift-that-sends-artwork-to-other-museums-180988597/</guid></item><item><title>仿人机器人在中国比赛中打破了人类最快半程马拉松世界纪录</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-humanoid-robot-just-beat-the-human-world-record-for-the-fastest-half-marathon-during-a-race-in-china-180988599/</link><description>由中国电子公司荣耀开发的名为“闪电”的自动导航机器人赢得了 13.1 英里的比赛。其成绩和其他成绩标志着自去年首届赛事以来取得的重大进步，当时 21 名机器人中只有 6 人到达了终点线</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 19:27:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-humanoid-robot-just-beat-the-human-world-record-for-the-fastest-half-marathon-during-a-race-in-china-180988599/</guid></item><item><title>旧金山的稀有硬币寻宝游戏为参与者提供了重温加州淘金热的机会</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-coin-scavenger-hunt-in-san-francisco-offers-participants-the-chance-to-relive-the-california-gold-rush-180988598/</link><description>当地一家硬币经销商将在 4 月 25 日举办的第三届年度全市挑战赛中隐藏价值总计 50,000 美元的历史货币</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 18:42:31 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-rare-coin-scavenger-hunt-in-san-francisco-offers-participants-the-chance-to-relive-the-california-gold-rush-180988598/</guid></item><item><title>人类仍在进化。一项研究表明，自然选择青睐与红头发和较少男性型秃发有关的基因</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humans-are-still-evolving-natural-selection-has-favored-genes-linked-to-red-hair-and-less-male-pattern-baldness-a-study-suggests-180988563/</link><description>对数千名西欧亚人的古代和现代 DNA 进行的大规模研究发现了近 500 种近代历史上进化选择支持或反对的遗传变异</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 17:34:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humans-are-still-evolving-natural-selection-has-favored-genes-linked-to-red-hair-and-less-male-pattern-baldness-a-study-suggests-180988563/</guid></item><item><title>半个多世纪后，鲍勃·迪伦的《我不在那儿》的原始打字稿歌词被重新发现</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bob-dylans-original-typewritten-draft-lyrics-for-im-not-there-have-been-rediscovered-after-more-than-half-a-century-180988592/</link><description>几十年来，热心的歌迷只能在盗版黑胶唱片上听到这首晦涩难懂的歌曲。歌词草稿位于艾伦·金斯伯格 (Allen Ginsberg) 诗歌的第一版副本中，刚刚在拍卖会上以 6,800 美元的价格售出</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 16:15:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/bob-dylans-original-typewritten-draft-lyrics-for-im-not-there-have-been-rediscovered-after-more-than-half-a-century-180988592/</guid></item><item><title>一项研究表明，我们使用许多相同的脑细胞来观察和想象物体。这些发现为了解记忆提供了一个新窗口</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/we-use-many-of-the-same-brain-cells-to-see-and-to-imagine-objects-a-study-suggests-the-findings-provide-a-new-window-into-memory-180988580/</link><description>虽然过去的研究暗示相关大脑区域存在重叠，但新的研究深入到了细胞水平。这一发现可能有助于改善记忆障碍（如痴呆症）和某些精神疾病（如精神分裂症）的治疗</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/we-use-many-of-the-same-brain-cells-to-see-and-to-imagine-objects-a-study-suggests-the-findings-provide-a-new-window-into-memory-180988580/</guid></item><item><title>这个令人眼花缭乱的蒂芙尼彩色玻璃窗装饰了一座教堂一个多世纪。现在它需要一个新家</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-dazzling-tiffany-stained-glass-window-adorned-a-church-for-more-than-a-century-now-it-needs-a-new-home-180988590/</link><description>康涅狄格州温斯特德第二公理会教堂将拍卖以令人惊叹的瀑布和日落为特色的色彩缤纷的艺术品</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-dazzling-tiffany-stained-glass-window-adorned-a-church-for-more-than-a-century-now-it-needs-a-new-home-180988590/</guid></item><item><title>纽约市公墓修复了一座维多利亚时期的温室，欢迎游客来到其历史悠久的土地</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/green-wood-cemetery-restored-a-victorian-greenhouse-to-welcome-visitors-to-its-historic-grounds-180988588/</link><description>布鲁克林的格林伍德公墓源于 19 世纪的“乡村公墓”运动，该运动将墓地从狭窄、黑暗变成了广阔而美丽</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 20:35:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/green-wood-cemetery-restored-a-victorian-greenhouse-to-welcome-visitors-to-its-historic-grounds-180988588/</guid></item><item><title>宇航员对地球引力的记忆可能会影响他们移动和握住物体的方式，即使在太空中呆了几个月后也是如此</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronauts-memories-of-earths-gravity-may-influence-how-they-move-and-hold-objects-even-after-months-in-space-180988586/</link><description>科学家表示，检查太空旅行者的精细运动技能有助于提高未来任务的安全性</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 20:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/astronauts-memories-of-earths-gravity-may-influence-how-they-move-and-hold-objects-even-after-months-in-space-180988586/</guid></item><item><title>一位诗人的爱情故事被缩短后，他的信件神秘消失——直到善本经销商凭预感采取行动</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-john-keats-love-story-was-cut-short-his-letters-mysteriously-disappeared-until-rare-book-dealers-acted-on-a-hunch-180988585/</link><description>约翰济慈在英年早逝之前写给未婚妻的八封信是“一生的文学发现”</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 18:53:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-john-keats-love-story-was-cut-short-his-letters-mysteriously-disappeared-until-rare-book-dealers-acted-on-a-hunch-180988585/</guid></item><item><title>新西兰一只残疾鹦鹉凭借其创新的战斗方式成为雄性领袖</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/disabled-parrot-in-new-zealand-became-alpha-male-thanks-to-his-innovative-fighting-style-180988587/</link><description>研究人员在一项新研究中表示，啄羊鹦鹉的半喙变成了优势而不是劣势</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 18:46:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/disabled-parrot-in-new-zealand-became-alpha-male-thanks-to-his-innovative-fighting-style-180988587/</guid></item><item><title>裸鼹鼠通常会通过决斗来选择下一个女王。但这些不寻常的啮齿动物可能能够进行更和平的权力过渡</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/naked-mole-rats-usually-duke-it-out-to-decide-who-becomes-a-colonys-next-queen-but-these-unusual-creatures-are-also-capable-of-peaceful-transitions-new-research-suggests-180988589/</link><description>在一项以“Amigos”群体为中心的实验室实验中，研究人员观察到，一只从属雌性顺利接管了繁殖任务。</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 18:37:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/naked-mole-rats-usually-duke-it-out-to-decide-who-becomes-a-colonys-next-queen-but-these-unusual-creatures-are-also-capable-of-peaceful-transitions-new-research-suggests-180988589/</guid></item><item><title>新的考古发现揭示了圣安东尼奥最早的定居者如何灌溉农作物和获取饮用水</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-archaeological-discoveries-reveal-how-san-antonio-colonists-irrigated-crops-and-accessed-drinking-water-180988571/</link><description>在准备学校翻修时，德克萨斯州的研究人员发现了历史悠久的 San Pedro acequia 的遗迹，这是一种拥有数百年历史的技术，为这个新兴的村庄提供水源</description><pubDate>Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:26:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-archaeological-discoveries-reveal-how-san-antonio-colonists-irrigated-crops-and-accessed-drinking-water-180988571/</guid></item><item><title>文艺复兴时期的艺术将美与美德、丑与恶联系起来。了解从达芬奇到波提切利的画家如何看待外表吸引力</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/sm