能不仅用它们来吸引猎物，还用它们与潜在的配偶交流</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 21:41:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/anglerfish-are-known-for-their-built-in-fishing-rods-new-research-sheds-light-on-how-these-lures-evolved-in-the-strange-creatures-180988577/</guid></item><item><title>本周抬头即可看到天琴座流星雨的顶峰。 2700 年来，人类一直在记录这一令人眼花缭乱的年度展示</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/look-up-this-week-to-see-the-peak-of-the-lyrid-meteor-shower-humans-have-documented-this-dazzling-display-for-2700-years-180988578/</link><description>4 月 22 日凌晨，月落时间将为美国大部分地区的观星者在日出前呈现一片漆黑的天空</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 19:48:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/look-up-this-week-to-see-the-peak-of-the-lyrid-meteor-shower-humans-have-documented-this-dazzling-display-for-2700-years-180988578/</guid></item><item><title>科学家在纽约公墓下发现了 560 万只穴居蜂。该集团是有记录以来最大的集团之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-found-5-6-million-burrowing-bees-beneath-a-cemetery-in-new-york-the-group-is-one-of-the-largest-on-record-180988573/</link><description>伊萨卡的研究人员估计了 2023 年春季从当地墓地出现的地面筑巢蜜蜂的数量，揭示了一些未被充分研究的传粉媒介的数量</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 19:12:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-found-5-6-million-burrowing-bees-beneath-a-cemetery-in-new-york-the-group-is-one-of-the-largest-on-record-180988573/</guid></item><item><title>泰坦尼克号载有 3500 件救生衣，但几乎全部都消失在历史之中。这件作品刚刚在拍卖会上以近 100 万美元的价格售出</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-titanic-carried-3500-life-jackets-but-almost-all-of-them-have-been-lost-to-history-this-one-just-sold-at-auction-for-nearly-1-million-180988574/</link><description>这件文物属于头等舱乘客劳拉·梅贝尔·弗朗卡特利 (Laura Mabel Francatelli)，她是一名秘书，正与雇主一起前往芝加哥。这是唯一一件出现在拍卖会上的与 1912 年海难幸存者有关的救生衣</description><pubDate>Mon, 20 Apr 2026 19:11:49 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-titanic-carried-3500-life-jackets-but-almost-all-of-them-have-been-lost-to-history-this-one-just-sold-at-auction-for-nearly-1-million-180988574/</guid></item></channel></rss>